Interface Network<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAdaptable, IMultiNet, INetBranchElement<TBus,TBranch>, INetBusElement<TBus>, INetworkElement, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AclfNetwork, AcscNetwork, BaseAclfNetwork<TBus,TBranch>, BaseAcscNetwork<TBus,TBranch>, BaseDStabNetwork<TBus,TBra>, BaseOpfNetwork, DclfOpfNetwork, DistNetwork, DStab3PNetwork, DStabilityNetwork, Dynamic3PNetwork, OpfNetwork, Steady3PNetwork
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AclfNetworkImpl, AcscNetworkImpl, BaseAclfNetworkImpl, BaseAcscNetworkImpl, BaseDStabNetworkImpl, BaseOpfNetworkImpl, DclfOpfNetworkImpl, DistNetworkImpl, DStabilityNetworkImpl, Dynamic3PNetworkImpl, NetworkImpl, OpfNetworkImpl, Steady3PNetworkImpl

    public interface Network<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>
extends NameTag, IAdaptable, INetworkElement, INetBusElement<TBus>, INetBranchElement<TBus,TBranch>, IMultiNet
    A representation of the model object 'work'. The base network container class for storing buses and branches to format a power network.

    The following features are supported:

    • Base Kva
    • Frequency
    • Bus Number Arranged
    • Data Checked
    • Bypass Data Check
    • Allow Ground Branch
    • Switch Break Model
    • Original Data Format
    • Ref Bus Type
    • Ref Bus Id
    • Branch List
    • Bus List
    • Zone List
    • Area List
    • Tie Line List
    • Owner List
    • Child Net List
    See Also:
    NetPackage.getNetwork()

      • isSwitchBreakModel

        boolean isSwitchBreakModel()
        Returns the value of the 'Switch Break Model' attribute. The default value is "false".

        If the meaning of the 'Switch Break Model' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

        If true, allow to define bus section and dummy bus at branch for the switch/break model. The switch/break model is implemented using the bus section concept and child branch concept. It is independent of the zero Z branch concept. Zero Z branch could be used to create a switch/break network model.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Switch Break Model' attribute.
        See Also:
        setSwitchBreakModel(boolean), NetPackage.getNetwork_SwitchBreakModel()
